CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 22, 1955, pg. 11, reads: "Sweet Sixteen - Soaring with the stars on the magic sixteenth birthday, was Bootsie Bray, center, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. LuGene Bray, of Iowa Street. Some eighty or more young set members came to the gay party which celebrated the happy event.  Left to right: Buddie and Toni Bray, Kay Stokes, Marva Jo Hord, Gay Cyrus, and on the far right, Carol Jones. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Buddie Bray, Toni Bray, Kay Stokes, Marva Jo Hord, LouJeanne "Boostie" Bray wearing corsage and holding wrapped gifts on her sixteen birthday, Gay Cyrus, and Carol Jones, in Bray home on Iowa Street
